                                         MPUMALANGA - ANC deputy president Cyril Ramaphosa is addressing Cosatu Emalahleni Cadres Forum in Mpumalanga.  The event is also aimed at celebrating the legacy of the late ANC stalwart Oliver Reginald Tambo.  The ANC in Mpumalanga is considered to be a kingmaker in the 54th ANC Conference in December as it will be sending the second biggest voting delegation to the conference. WATCH: Cyril Ramaphosa addresses the Cosatu Emalahleni Cadres Forum 